## M5(3/n): integer literals adapt to declared sized integer types.
##
## Without literal pseudo-types this would type-error: `Int` is unsized
## and `U8` is sized, so a strict same-type rule rejects them. With
## literal pseudo-types, `0` (an int_literal) is compatible with any
## integer type at use sites.
##
## EXPECTED: clean (no diagnostics).

sub main()
  x: U8 = 0
  y: I32 = -1
  z: F64 = 3.14
  print x
  print y
  print z
